BBT Alabama, LLC Statement of Operating Conditions for Transportation Service Record: 8-Section 8 (Nominations, Confirmation, Balancing, Cash-Out, and Penalties) Issued: September 1, 2023 Version: (2.0.0)
Effective: September 1, 2023
8. NOMINATION, CONFIRMATION, BALANCING, CASH-OUTS, AND PENALTIES 8.1 Required Information. (a) Within five (5) Business Days prior to the beginning of the Month, Shipper or its representative shall submit via Transporter's Transactional System to Transporter Shipper's best estimate of its daily requirements for Transportation from each of the Receipt Points and to each of the Delivery Points for the following Month. Such estimates shall be stated in Dekatherms. (b) Shipper shall nominate gas by notifying Transporter of the daily quantity of gas in Dekatherms it has available at the Receipt Points ("Receipt Point Nominated Quantities") and of the quantity of gas it desires to have delivered at the Delivery Points ("Delivery Point Nominated Quantities"). The total volumes to be delivered for the account of Shipper by Transporter must equal the total receipt nominations plus FL&U, if applicable, and any other adjustments provided in the definition of Equivalent Thermal Quantities. (c) All nominations shall include Shipper-defined begin dates and end dates. All nominations should have roll-over options. Specifically, Shippers should have the ability to nominate for several Days or a Month, provided the nomination begin and end dates are within the term of the Shipper's contract. (d) All nominations shall include the following components: Delivery location, delivery rank, Downstream ID ("Dn ID"), quantity, receipt location, receipt rank, Upstream ID ("Up ID"), service requestor, transaction type, and such other information as Transporter may request from Shipper. 8.2 Calculation of Time. All times listed in this Section 8 are Central Clock Time. 8.3 Form of Nomination. Nominations must be submitted in writing via the Transactional System and must include the information specified in Section 8.1 of this Statement of Operating Conditions. 8.4 Nomination Cycles. A Shipper may avail itself of the daily nomination cycles promulgated by NAESB and adopted, to the extent codified, by FERC in its regulations. 8.5 Confirmation of Nominated Quantities. (a) All nominations will be confirmed by the upstream or downstream connected party through the Internet Homepage or EDI. At least one service provider (including a point operator) shall provide a confirmation for a quantity of gas with respect to a nomination at a location on each side of a physical location. (b) With respect to the timely nomination or confirmation process at a Receipt Point or Delivery Point, in the absence of agreement to the contrary, the lesser of the confirmation quantities will be the confirmed quantity. If a Shipper does not respond to a request for confirmation or if the confirmation response is unsolicited, the lesser of the confirmation quantity or the previously scheduled quantity will be the new confirmed quantity. (c) With respect to the processing of requests for increases during the intra-day nomination or confirmation process, in the absence of agreement to the contrary, the lesser of the confirmation quantities will be the new confirmed quantity. If a Shipper does not respond to a request for confirmation or if the confirmation response is unsolicited, the previously scheduled quantity will be the new confirmed quantity. 8.6 Delegation of Nomination Authority to Agent. A Shipper may delegate to any third party (an "Agent") the responsibility for submitting nominations and receiving confirmations or performing other administrative duties under any Service Agreement, subject to the following conditions: (a) Any designation of a third party as agent, or any change in such designation, must be provided in writing to Transporter at least two (2) Business Days prior to the requested effective date of the designation. (b) The written designation shall specify any limits on the authority of the Agent, including any time limit for the designation. (c) Transporter will rely on communications from a Shipper's Agent for all nomination purposes except to the extent the designation is explicitly limited. Limitations must be clearly specified. Shipper will hold Transporter harmless and shall indemnify Transporter for any losses incurred by Transporter in the event Transporter's good faith interpretation of a limitation proves inconsistent with the intent of the limitation. Transporter reserves the right to reject delegations for reasons of unclear or impracticable limitations placed thereon. Communications by Transporter to such Agent shall be deemed notice to Shipper except to the extent the Agent's authority is explicitly limited as follows: (i) With respect to the receipt of notice, the provisions of this Statement. (ii) With respect to an Agent for one or more Shippers, any third party may administer multiple Service Agreements; however, the Agent shall administer and account separately for each Service Agreement. (iii) With respect to an Agent's authority, each Agent must execute the Agency Agreement in the form posted on Transporter's Internet Website prior to being authorized to act for a Shipper. (d) Scheduled quantities will be received and delivered at a uniform hourly rate of scheduled quantity divided by 24. Transporter, in its reasonable discretion, shall have the right to accept variations from such hourly rates. 8.7 Balancing and Cash-Out. (a) Due to Transporter's need to allocate unused capacity to Shippers in an efficient and systematic manner, Shipper or its representative may be required to balance, on a daily, monthly, or other basis, its nominations with its actual deliveries of Gas to Transporter at the Receipt Points as well as redeliveries of gas to Shipper or its representatives at the Delivery Points. (b) Shipper and Transporter also intend that the quantity of Gas actually received each Day at the Receipt Points will be Equivalent Thermal Quantity to the actual quantity of Gas allocated to Shipper at the Delivery Points. Any imbalance created when the actual physical quantity of Gas at the Receipt Points (adjusted for FL&U) is different than the actual quantity of Gas allocated to Shipper at the Delivery Points will be the "Operational Imbalance." The correction of any Operating Imbalance will be the responsibility of the Shipper. (c) The best available operating flow data at the Receipt Points and the Delivery Points shall be used during the current period to determine the estimated Operational Imbalance with physical or nominated quantity adjustments to be made during the current period to attempt to maintain or achieve an Operational Imbalance of zero. (d) Associated with each Operational Imbalance at the end of each Month shall be a percentage which shall be calculated by dividing the quantities of Gas received by Transporter from Shipper at the Receipt Points, less FL&U, by the quantity of Gas delivered by Transporter to or for Shipper at the Delivery Points. The Operational Imbalance will be cashed out by multiplying the Operational Imbalance expressed in MMBtus by the percentage listed ("Cash-Out Percentage") corresponding to the percentage associated with the Operational Imbalance and then multiplying the product by the Cash-Out Price. The "Cash-Out Price" on Transporter's System shall be a weighted-average price determined by (i) calculating a percentage for each interconnecting pipeline with Transporter by dividing the amount of gas nominated at each interconnecting pipeline location that Month by the total amount of gas nominated at all interconnecting pipeline locations that Month and (ii) multiplying each percentage by the actual cash out price set forth in Transporter's then-effective operational balancing agreement ("OBA") with each of the interconnecting pipelines. For the sake of clarity, the actual cash out price set forth in Transporter's currently effective OBA with TGP will be the "Average Monthly Market Area Regional Price" and can be found at https://pipeline2.kindermorgan.com/Notices/Notices.aspx?type=N&code=TGP (Non Critical Notices page); the actual cash out price set forth in Transporter's currently effective OBA with Transco is for "Zones 4, 4A, 4B" and cash-out provisions are set forth in Transco's FERC Gas Tariff, Fifth Revised Volume No. 1, Part IV-GENERAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS; SECTION 37, CASH OUT PROVISIONS, and can be found at 1line.williams.com/Transco/index.html; and the actual cash out price set forth in Transporter's currently effective OBA with SNG, which is referenced in Section 14.1 of the General Terms and Conditions of SNG's FERC Gas Tariff, is provided to Transporter via monthly invoice. . If the Operational Imbalance is greater than 100%, payment will be made by Transporter to Shipper. If the Operational Imbalance is less than 100%, payment will be made by Shipper to Transporter. On a non-discriminatory basis, Transporter and Shipper may mutually agree to a Cash-Out Price different than that set forth in this Section 8.7(d). (e) If Transporter reasonably determines that due to operational constraints or otherwise it cannot reasonably enforce any or all of the provisions of Sections 8.7(a), 8.7(b), 8.7(c), 8.7(d), or 8.7(e) hereof, it may in its discretion waive any or all of such provisions. Any such waiver shall be applied on a not unduly discriminatory basis. (f) An event of Force Majeure, as defined in Section 18 hereof, shall not excuse Shipper from the operation of the provisions of Sections 8.7(a), 8.7(b), 8.7(c), 8.7(d), or 8.7(e) hereof inasmuch as Shipper would be able to control its imbalances by adjusting its actual deliveries to Transporter at the Receipt Point or its Delivery Point Nominated Quantities. 8.8 Unauthorized Overrun. For any Unauthorized Overrun, Transporter may impose on Shipper (x) the maximum Service charge plus (y) a charge equal to the daily price of Gas listed for that Day as follows: the higher of (i) Platts Gas Daily publication midpoint price listed as the Tennessee, 500 Leg index and (ii) Platts Gas Daily publication midpoint price listed as the Transco, zone 4 index (or if either index is unavailable, another similar publication), plus (z) five dollars ($5.00) per MMBtu. For the sake of clarity, Transporter may impose on Shipper the sum of (x), (y), and (z) for unauthorized overrun service. In addition, the quantity delivered in excess of the MDQ shall be charged the Authorized Overrun service charge as provided in the applicable rate schedule of Shipper. 8.9 Billing and Payment. Billing and payment of the cash-out and applicable penalties described above shall be pursuant to Section 15 hereof. 8.10 Balancing upon Termination. Upon termination of a Transportation Agreement, Shipper shall have thirty (30) Days to correct any remaining imbalances. After this period has elapsed, Transporter shall have the right to retain any positive imbalance quantity without compensation to the Shipper and shall assess, in addition to all other penalties set forth in this Section 8, a charge of five dollars ($5.00) per MMBtu for any negative imbalance quantity as applicable.
